<section class="detail" id="blit/6">


    <span id="blit/5"></span>

  <div class="detail-header">
    <a href="#blit/6" class="detail-link" data-no-tooltip="" aria-label="Link to this function">
      <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
    <div class="heading-with-actions">

        <div class="signature-row">
          <h1 class="signature" translate="no">blit(This, Dest, Size, Source, Src)<span class="signature-arrow">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span><span class="signature-result">blit(This, Dest, Size, Source, Src, [])</span></h1>


            <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/wx/src/gen/wxDC.erl#L163" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
              <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </a>

        </div>

      <div class="signature-row">

          <h1 class="signature" translate="no">blit/6</h1>



          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/wx/src/gen/wxDC.erl#L193" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">



        <div class="specs">

            <pre translate="no"><span class="attribute">-spec</span> blit(This, Dest, Size, Source, Src) -> <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:boolean/0">boolean</a>()
              when
                  This :: <a href="#t:wxDC/0">wxDC</a>(),
                  Dest :: {X :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>(), Y :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>()},
                  Size :: {W :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>(), H :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>()},
                  Source :: <a href="#t:wxDC/0">wxDC</a>(),
                  Src :: {X :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>(), Y :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>()}.</pre>

            <pre translate="no"><span class="attribute">-spec</span> blit(This, Dest, Size, Source, Src, [Option]) -> <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:boolean/0">boolean</a>()
              when
                  This :: <a href="#t:wxDC/0">wxDC</a>(),
                  Dest :: {X :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>(), Y :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>()},
                  Size :: {W :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>(), H :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>()},
                  Source :: <a href="#t:wxDC/0">wxDC</a>(),
                  Src :: {X :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>(), Y :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>()},
                  Option ::
                      {rop, <a href="wx.html#t:wx_enum/0">wx:wx_enum</a>()} |
                      {useMask, <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:boolean/0">boolean</a>()} |
                      {srcPtMask, {X :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>(), Y :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>()}}.</pre>

        </div>


<p>Copy from a source DC to this DC.</p><p>With this method you can specify the destination coordinates and the size of area to copy
which will be the same for both the source and target DCs. If you need to apply scaling
while copying, use <code class="inline">StretchBlit()</code> (not implemented in wx).</p><p>Notice that source DC coordinates <code class="inline">xsrc</code> and <code class="inline">ysrc</code> are interpreted using the current
source DC coordinate system, i.e. the scale, origin position and axis directions are taken
into account when transforming them to physical (pixel) coordinates.</p><p>Remark: There is partial support for <a href="#blit/6"><code class="inline">blit/6</code></a> in <a href="wxPostScriptDC.html"><code class="inline">wxPostScriptDC</code></a>, under X.</p><p>See:</p><ul><li><p><a href="wxMemoryDC.html"><code class="inline">wxMemoryDC</code></a></p></li><li><p><a href="wxBitmap.html"><code class="inline">wxBitmap</code></a></p></li><li><p><a href="wxMask.html"><code class="inline">wxMask</code></a></p></li></ul>
  </section>
</section>
<section class="detail" id="calcBoundingBox/3">


  <div class="detail-header">
    <a href="#calcBoundingBox/3" class="detail-link" data-no-tooltip="" aria-label="Link to this function">
      <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
    <div class="heading-with-actions">

      <div class="signature-row">


            <h1 class="signature" translate="no">calcBoundingBox(This :: <a href="#t:wxDC/0">wxDC</a>(), X :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>(), Y :: <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>())<span class="signature-arrow">&nbsp;-&gt;&nbsp;</span><span class="signature-result">ok</span></h1>




          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/wx/src/gen/wxDC.erl#L213" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">


        <div class="specs">
          <h4 class="specs-title">Types</h4>

            <pre translate="no">X = Y = <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:integer/0">integer</a>()</pre>

        </div>


<p>Adds the specified point to the bounding box which can be retrieved with <a href="#minX/1"><code class="inline">minX/1</code></a>, <a href="#maxX/1"><code class="inline">maxX/1</code></a>
and <a href="#minY/1"><code class="inline">minY/1</code></a>, <a href="#maxY/1"><code class="inline">maxY/1</code></a> functions.</p><p>See: <a href="#resetBoundingBox/1"><code class="inline">resetBoundingBox/1</code></a></p>
  </section>
</section>
<section class="detail" id="clear/1">


  <div class="detail-header">
    <a href="#clear/1" class="detail-link" data-no-tooltip="" aria-label="Link to this function">
      <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
    <div class="heading-with-actions">

      <div class="signature-row">


            <h1 class="signature" translate="no">clear(This :: <a href="#t:wxDC/0">wxDC</a>())<span class="signature-arrow">&nbsp;-&gt;&nbsp;</span><span class="signature-result">ok</span></h1>




          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/wx/src/gen/wxDC.erl#L228" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">



<p>Clears the device context using the current background brush.</p><p>Note that <a href="#setBackground/2"><code class="inline">setBackground/2</code></a> method must be used to set the brush used by <a href="#clear/1"><code class="inline">clear/1</code></a>, the brush used for filling the
shapes set by <a href="#setBrush/2"><code class="inline">setBrush/2</code></a> is ignored by it.</p><p>If no background brush was set, solid white brush is used to clear the device context.</p>
  </section>
</section>
